dence between TC-Y and HCG. The size of this threshold 
was arbitrarily set large enough to exceed any random 
interindividual and intraindividual variation in both cog­
nitive test scores and the change in scores with time, 
because of their slow decline in individuals aged 50 years 
or older.14 Other trials have also used a threshold-based 
